Boxley Materials Company, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 27, 2017 1:27 AM ET
Construction Materials

Company Overview of Boxley Materials Company, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Boxley Materials Company, Inc. manufactures and supplies crushed limestone, granite, and sandstone to contractors and construction managers. It offers base stone products that are used for stabilization beneath asphalt and concrete paving for parking lots and highways; course aggregates that are used in asphalt and concrete mixes, and on driveways and for septic systems; and fine aggregates. The company also provides large rocks that are used along shorelines of rivers and lakes to help with erosion control, as well as for landscaping purposes; agricultural lime products that are used by farmers and homeowners to raise the PH level in soils to promote healthy fields and lawns; other material...
Boxley Materials Company, Inc. manufactures and supplies crushed limestone, granite, and sandstone to contractors and construction managers. It offers base stone products that are used for stabilization beneath asphalt and concrete paving for parking lots and highways; course aggregates that are used in asphalt and concrete mixes, and on driveways and for septic systems; and fine aggregates. The company also provides large rocks that are used along shorelines of rivers and lakes to help with erosion control, as well as for landscaping purposes; agricultural lime products that are used by farmers and homeowners to raise the PH level in soils to promote healthy fields and lawns; other materials for logging and farms roads; and fine aggregate products (manufactured sands). Further, it offers hot, warm, and cold mix asphalt products, as well as porous asphalt pavement; blocks, bricks, and hardscapes; and concrete products. In addition, it provides paving contracting and maintenance services for streets and highways, commercial services, site prep/grading, curb and gutter, tennis courts, and airports. The company was founded in 1892 and is based in Blue Ridge, Virginia with locations in Lynchburg, Concord, Martinsville, Arrington, Low Moor, Roanoke, Salem, and Wytheville; Virginia. As of March 18, 2016, Boxley Materials Company, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Summit Materials, Inc.
Detailed Description


